# Grey-Seal — Cursor Rules

See `docs/CONVENTIONS.md` for the full convention reference.

## Language & Runtime

- Go 1.26, module `github.com/holmes89/grey-seal`
- All code must pass `go vet ./...` and `golangci-lint run ./...`

## Project Structure

```
cmd/api/          ConnectRPC HTTP/2 server + shrikeSearcher adapter
cmd/worker/       Kafka consumer runner
lib/greyseal/     Domain packages: conversation, resource, role
lib/repo/         PostgreSQL connection + repositories
lib/repo/ollama/  Ollama LLM adapter
lib/repo/cache/   Redis resource cache adapter
lib/schemas/      Generated protobuf — never edit
```

## Domain Package Layout

Each `lib/greyseal/<entity>/` must have:
- `interface.go` — exported service interface + types
- `service.go` — unexported impl; starts with `var _ EntityService = (*entityService)(nil)`
- `grpc/service.go` — ConnectRPC handler
- `mocks/` — mockery output, never hand-edited

## Code Patterns

### Constructor returns interface

```go
func NewConversationService(..., logger *zap.Logger) ConversationService {
    return &conversationService{...}
}
```

### Optional dependencies pattern (env-var gated)

```go
// In main.go — pass nil when env var absent
var resourceCache conversationsvc.ResourceCache
if redisURL := os.Getenv("REDIS_URL"); redisURL != "" {
    rdb := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{Addr: redisURL})
    resourceCache = cache.NewRedisResourceCache(rdb)
}
```

### Shrike adapter (keeps domain clean)

```go
type shrikeSearcher struct{ client shrikeconnect.SearchServiceClient }
func (s *shrikeSearcher) Search(ctx context.Context, query string, limit int32, resourceUUIDs []string) ([]conversationsvc.SearchResult, error)
```

## Testing

- Unit: `package conversation_test`, testify/suite, `zap.NewNop()`, mockery mocks
- Integration: `//go:build integration`, dockertest `postgres:16-alpine`, no mocks
- Never mock the database in integration tests

## Observability

- `initOTel(ctx, "grey-seal", logger)` — noop if `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` unset
- DB: `github.com/XSAM/otelsql` (not `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/…/otelsql`)
- HTTP: `otelhttp.NewHandler(mux, "grey-seal")`

## Banned Patterns

- Hand-editing `lib/schemas/` — generated code only
- Raw SQL strings in repository code — use squirrel
- Returning concrete types from constructors — return interfaces
- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/database/sql/otelsql` — does not exist
- Mocking the DB in integration tests
